  "outlines": {
    "toc": "<ol xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n\t\t\t\t<li>If YouWere a Horse</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>All About Horses</li>\n\t\t\t</ol>",
    "headings": "<ul><li><span class=\"toc-h1\">If YouWere a Horse</span><li><span class=\"toc-h1\">All About Horses</span><ul><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">A horse’s powerful legs help the animal run far and jump high. Some horses can run more than 50 miles per hour!</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">A white spot at a horse’s eye level or above is called a star. Any white mark below its eyes but above its nostrils is called a stripe.</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">Did you know that a zebra is a type of horse?</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">Some miniature (MIN-ee-uh-chur)</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">horses are trained to help blind people.</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">They are like seeing-eye dogs.</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">A horse has only one toe on each foot. Each toe is covered by a horny hoof.A horseshoe is used to protect the hoof.</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">A muzzle is a horse’s jaw and nose. The withers are the ridge between a horse’s two shoulder bones.</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">Contents</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">Page List</span><li><span class=\"toc-h2\">Landmarks</span></li></ul></li></ul>",
    "html": "<ol><li></li></ol>"
  },
